NAME
       simple_shell - Holberton School project shell

SYNOPSIS
       simple_shell

DESCRIPTION
       simple_shell is a basic Unix shell developed as a project for Holberton
       School. It provides a command-line interface for users to interact with
       the operating system.

OPTIONS
       None.

COMMANDS
       The shell supports various standard shell commands including:

       - ls: List directory contents.
       - env: Print current enviroment.
       - exit: Exit the shell.

LIMITATIONS
      If a command is used that was not posted in the project requiremeents (e.g. echo) then and Error will show

AUTHORS
       simple_shell was developed by Venghour Heng, Lachlan Luchetti, and Anthony Joy as a Holberton
       School project.

BUGS
